		<div class="comment_text"><p>Ray, I just went through a whole ordeal with Dell, and I'm not entirely happy.  I've owned 9 Dell machines since 1997, this being my tenth.</p><p>I made the order on March 6th, and on the 19th I got an e-mail stating the order was cancelled.  I called and was told that some parts were out of stock and had to be replaced with different parts.  OK, a new order was placed by their system.  On the 27th I'd not heard anything so I logged into my Dell account, "Order Cancelled"..??? WTH?  I called again and was told there was an issue with my Dell Preferred account.  Had to wait until the next day to call as that dept. is only open 9-5 Eastern.  No issue with the Dell Preferred account, but the issue was that machine was no longer in inventory, they don't sell it anymore.</p><p>So I was transferred to a sales person, and explained what I wanted, based on my original order config, and was told it would be about $100 more for a similar system.  OK, that's fine... Got this machine on April 8th... Loved it... AMD x4 processor, 64-bit, 6-GB ram, 1-TB hdd... only thing missing from what I was sure I asked for was dual-video support, but they build sheet didn't have that so I ignored this and put in a video card with dual-support that I had lying around.</p><p>Then four days later the system was dead.  Power it on, and it stayed on for about 10-15 secs and then powered off.  I was on the phone with Dell for about 2 hours, trying this, trying that, and eventually the tech asked if I wanted to replace the system... and we'll up the memory to 8-GB from the 6 in there... OK, that will work...</p><p>Waited, then on April 23rd I was notified that the order was cancelled... I was really pissed at this point, as I should have just simply gone to Best Buy and bought something off the shelf!  Anyway, I called them again and now this model of Inspiron is no longer made...  UGH!   So the tech says that I can get a new model, nothing additional for me to pay, so I take the Inspiron 580, and since the MB doesn't support AMD I'll have to have Intel, again fine with me as I'm not paying for the upgrade... they ship it out and I got it on May 4th... two months after my original order!!!!</p><p>So I set it up, and argh!!! only 6-GB of ram... OMG!  So again I call, and the tech is saying stuff like you got a processor upgrade, etc., etc... and I ask him to look back through the notes of the last conversations I had and there it is, a Dell tech, and his manager telling be I'll get 8-GB... the other upgrades are on Dell as they machine is no longer made.  So he gets on with his manager, it gets OK'd and they send me another 2-GB...</p><p>So, now I'm happy that I have my new system, but I'm sure confused about my loyalty to Dell at this point.  I'm sure that I will buy from them again, but this was a hard situation to swallow...</p><p>Sorry for the length, but I wanted to let you know how my recent purchase experience went.</p></div>
